!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

consent /kənˈsɛnt/

(consenting,consented,consents) 

1. N-UNCOUNT If you give your consent to something, you give someone permission to do it. 准许 [正式] 

例： At approximately 11:30 p.m., Pollard finally gave his consent to the search. 大约晚上11:30的时候，波拉德终于对搜查予以同意。 

2. V-T/V-I If you consent to something, you agree to do it or to allow it to be done. 同意 [正式] 

例： He finally consented to go. 他最终同意去。 

例： He asked Ginny if she would consent to a small celebration after the christening. 他问金尼她是否同意在洗礼仪式后来个小庆祝。 

3.  →  see also age of consent

</div>

